title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 5906TSW 9MM  TACTICAL in box RARE
postcontent: The Smith & Wesson 9MM 5906TSW was introduced in 2000 as the upgrade to the legendary 5906 which was popular with law enforcement throughout the 90's for its unmatched reliable durability.  Construction is all stainless steel with a 4" barrel and high capacity 15 round double stack magazine. The TSW (Tactical Support Weapon) features a rail under the frame for light or laser sight attachment, thicker full length frame rails for enhanced accuracy, and delayed unlocking to reduce felt recoil. That and it's 37.6 oz. weight makes this a highly controllable soft shooter for accurate follow up shots and comfortable fun at the range. The action is called Traditional Double Action (TDA) which describes a longer 1st shot trigger pull which cocks the hammer, and single action short crisp trigger pull on subsequent shots. An ambidextrous safety / decocker is featured for convenience and ultimate safety. There is also a loaded chamber indicator.This later production pistol I have for sale was made 1/26/2005. The factory Novak Lo-Mount 3 dot sights and recoil spring are new.It took me 2 years to find this model in good shape since those who have them simply don't let them go.It's been well cared for as you can see. There is normal carry wear including faded surface laser etching but the finish is really nice with no noticeable scratches. The internals are excellent since you simply can't wear out a 3rd Gen Smith. Along with a 2nd factory magazine, an S&W case, a box of top rated Hornady Critical Defense FTX self defense ammo, and an owner's manual are included. No trades please. Email Bill for phone #.
